The '''blue-and-white kingfisher''' ('''''Todiramphus diops''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Alcedinidae]].
It is [[endemic]] to [[North Maluku]] in [[Indonesia]]. It can be found on the islands of [[Morotai]], Ngelengele, [[Halmahera]], Damar, [[Ternate]], [[Tidore]], Moti, Bacan, Obi and Obilatu.<ref>{{cite book|last=Coates|first=Brian J.|title=A Guide to the Birds of Wallacea: Sulawesi, The Moluccas and the Lesser Sunda Islands, Indonesia|year=1997|publisher=Dove Publications|location=Alderley, Queensland|page=377|author2=K. David Bishop}}</ref>

Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical mangrove [[forest]]s.

